  "text": "All three phylogenetic analyses recovered the monophyly of Rhinocerotidae with high support (PP: 1.00; BS ( Historical distribution in Southeast Asia and origin of specimens used for molecular investigations of (A) the Javan rhinoceros (Rhinoceros sondaicus), with the only extant location on Java (1) and last extinct one in Vietnam (2), and (B) Sumatran rhinoceros (Dicerorhinus sumatrensis) with locations: 1 -Riau, Sumatra; 2 -Djambi, Sumatra; 3 -Bengkulu, Sumatra; 4 -Sabah, Borneo. Light shaded area: distribution given by [CITATION_1] ; dark shaded area: distribution given by [CITATION_2] . with moderately high to high support in the ML and MP analyses but was marginally not supported in the BI analysis (PP: 0.93; BS (ML): 85; BS (MP): 88, Fig. 4 ). The relationships of the clades including the African rhinoceroses, the clade composed of the Indian and the Javan rhinoceros and the clade including the woolly rhinoceros and the Sumatran rhinoceros were in all three analyses unresolved.",
